				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\sigma $\end{document} are determined. The smallest average value is kept as indicative of the average UV background during the whole period, and the corresponding RMS is used to determine the significance of the photon count fluctuations. A normalized photon count evolution is then produced by plotting the so-called significance signal, defined for GTU number i\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
